12. Conclusions & Overall Assessment
Overall Assessment:
  • Study Design: This was a single dose toxicity study (Gene Therapy Toxicology) in MONKEY CYNOMOLGUS (6 animals) via intravenous administration. Primary focus: biodistribution, immunogenicity, and target organ toxicity.
  • Mortality: All animals survived to scheduled sacrifice.
  • Body Weights: No significant treatment-related effects.
  • Clinical Pathology: No statistically significant treatment-related changes.
  • Immunogenicity: Neutralizing Binding Antidrug Antibody: responses comparable across groups (range: 81.67-81.67).
  • Pharmacokinetics: Pharmacokinetic summary: Protein Expression - 1E13 vg/kg, Vector A..: Cmax=23.54 % of normal at Day 29.0; 1E13 vg/kg, Vector B..: Cmax=33.85 % of normal at Day 43.0. Vector A - 1E13 vg/kg, Vector A..:
  • Pathology: Macroscopic findings present. Microscopic findings present. Treatment-related findings should be assessed for adversity.
  • Data Gaps: The following domains were not available: Food/Water Consumption, Organ Weights, Vital Signs.
